{
  "texts": [
    "Finally, for each epoch, dynamically changed masking patterns were applied to the training data.The recent LLMs have introduced many new uses for text generative AI.",
    "The Llama3 [21] model, a model based on transformer architectures such as RoBERTa, that was pre-trained on an extensive corpus of 15 trillion tokens of data, has allowed for the use of generative AI in sentiment analysis.",
    "The architecture of this model uses the Transformer architecture [67], a rotary positional embeddings [62] and the grouped-query attention (GQA) [2] with 8 keyvalue heads.",
    "During training, Llama3 uses an attention mask that prevents self-attention between different documents within the same sequence.",
    "Another model, MistralAI [37], implements Sliding Window Attention(SWA), Rolling Buffer Cache and Pre-fill and Chunking to reduce the number of neurons required."
  ]
}